benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: Multiple scenarios exercise removal of all or selected tags via tagDef and without tagDef.

Error Handling and Validation: Tests cover 400 (invalid ID, empty tagDef, malformed tagDef, missing or invalid header values), 404 (non-existent invoice item), 413 (too many tagDef values), 422 (invalid input in headers) as applicable.
Authorization: Tests ensure missing header (400) and invalid token (401).
Query Parameters Coverage: Extensive test of tagDef parameter combinations including valid, empty, missing, malformed, and extra parameters.
Edge cases and security: Tests include removing with special characters in headers and comments (XSS/Injection tests).
Integration/Regression: Tests for dependent services being unavailable (TC19) and regression scenario for special characters in comment (TC18).
Accessibility: TC20 ensures API docs and error messages accessible.
gaps: Soft Deletes: No explicit test confirming whether deletion is soft or hard, or a deleted flag is set.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Authorization Coverage: 403 Forbidden scenarios not covered (different roles).
Pagination: Not applicable to DELETE, but no tests about batch deletions or paginating results are present (if applicable).
Explicit race-condition scenarios: While TC17 covers concurrency, dedicated race-condition tests may be lacking.
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test for insufficient permissions to delete tags.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests (429) and test behavior under burst of requests.
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) on DELETE responses where applicable.
Add explicit tests for soft-delete semantics (if policy requires).
Add dedicated race-condition tests to ensure safety when multiple users delete concurrently.
Consider tests for batch deletions or other parameter edge cases not currently covered.
